info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 09 at 2:11PM MST until December 10 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 PM MST SUNDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...East Platte County and South Laramie Range Foothills including portions of Interstate 25 and 80 near Cheyenne and Wheatland. * WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to 5 PM MST Sunday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
